commentary: IAA image is difficult to read. On PAM 43278_55, the sign is more visible. In which case, the aspect of the sign does cohere with the scribal idiography of shin.

IAA Image is difficult to read. On PAM 43278_55, the sign is more visible. Baumgarten reads a waw; however, this is not so easily interpreted. The sign is horizontal on its axis, and this means it could be the right-most branch of heh, chet, daleth, zayin,
Baumgarten reads a dalet, but this reading is made on the basis of CD. The idiograph of the sign coheres with the dalet, but there are other possibilities. RECHECK
